nts have been drawn into secular logics-no longer the property of God but of the Muslim community-and shaped by the modern state and modern understandings of charity and property. Although these transformations have produced new kinds of loyalties and new ways of being in society, Moumtaz's ethnography reveals the furtive persistence of endowment practices that perpetuate older ways of thinking of one's self and one's responsibilities toward family and state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aCharitable uses, trusts, and foundations (Islamic law)zLebanon. 0aCharity laws and legislationzLebanon. 0aEndowmentszLebanon. 0aIslamxCharities. 0aWaqfzLebanon. 7aRELIGION / Islam / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975781zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975781zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975781/original  a978-3-11-073915-2 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075419-3 EBOO